Previous Research

Since 2006, IOM researchers have analyzed causes of unintended pregnancy including unsafe abortions and related deaths in Uzbekistan over the years in terms of closed case reports registered with the MoH in terms of inability to recall practicing unintended pregnancies cited to as having been usual or frequent.67 Secured data from the health department has consisted of information comprising diagnosis through the conclusion of an unintended pregnancy analysis based on diagnosis code in which unintended pregnancy deaths were recorded.68 In 2006, concerns of unintended pregnancy, unsafe abortion and unintended mortality formed the main source of research of international migratory information programs.69
